{
  "texts": [
    "Mike Sharples discusses the ways in which Generative AI can play the role of a possibility engine, a Socratic opponent, a co-designer, an exploratorium, or a storyteller (Sharples 2023: 3-5).",
    "Amy Stornaiuolo and colleagues show how learning to write with AI platforms can be fun (Stornaiuolo et al. 2024).Of course, for education applications we need to be wary of new versions of the digital divide with the rise of Generative AI.",
    "Owned by private companies, the free versions are only teasers to purchase better versions, and only some schools and students but not others will be able to afford the better versions.",
    "The COVID pandemic starkly highlighted the effects of these inequalities (Donnelly and Patrinos 2022).",
    "As educators, we also must maintain a critical eye on the processes of \"platformization\" (Nichols et al. 2024) (Cope and Kalantzis 2024a) and \"datafication\" (Pangrazio et al."
  ]
}